<BaseLayout title="Aaron Su — Portfolio">
  <section class="hero mx">
    <div class="hero-txt">
      <p class="greet">Hello, I'm</p>
      <h1>Aaron Su<br><span class="tw-wrap"><span id="tw"></span><span class="tw-cur"></span></span></h1>
      <p class="tag">Electrical &amp; computer engineering student at the <a href="https://www.ece.uw.edu/" target="_blank">University of Washington</a>. I design circuits, train models, and build things that bridge hardware and software.</p>
      <div class="status"><span class="dot"></span> Currently: <strong>Researching at <a href="http://uwseal.com/" target="_blank" style="color:inherit;border-bottom:1px solid var(--border)">SEAL Lab</a>, UW</strong> · Joining <a href="https://xmouyang.github.io/" target="_blank" style="color:inherit;border-bottom:1px solid var(--border)">HKUST MINSys Lab</a> Jun 2026</div>
      <div class="contacts">
        <a class="cl" href="mailto:awjsu@uw.edu"><svg width="16" height="16" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="1.5"><rect x="2" y="3" width="12" height="10" rx="2"/><path d="M2 5l6 4 6-4"/></svg> awjsu&#64;uw.edu</a>
        <a class="cl" href="https://linkedin.com/in/aaronsuuu/" target="_blank"><svg width="16" height="16" fill="currentColor"><path d="M2 3.5A1.5 1.5 0 0 1 3.5 2h9A1.5 1.5 0 0 1 14 3.5v9a1.5 1.5 0 0 1-1.5 1.5h-9A1.5 1.5 0 0 1 2 12.5v-9zM5.3 6.8v4.7h-1.6V6.8h1.6zm-.8-2.5a.93.93 0 1 1 0 1.86.93.93 0 0 1 0-1.86zM11.7 11.5h-1.6V9.2c0-.6-.2-1-.7-1-.4 0-.6.3-.7.5v2.8H7.1V6.8h1.5v.6c.2-.3.6-.7 1.4-.7 1 0 1.7.7 1.7 2.1v2.7z"/></svg> LinkedIn</a>
        <a class="cl" href="https://github.com/" target="_blank"><svg width="16" height="16" fill="currentColor"><path d="M8 1.5A6.5 6.5 0 0 0 5.94 14.2c.33.06.44-.14.44-.31v-1.1c-1.8.39-2.18-.87-2.18-.87-.3-.75-.72-.95-.72-.95-.59-.4.04-.4.04-.4.65.05 1 .67 1 .67.58.99 1.52.7 1.89.54.06-.42.23-.7.41-.87-1.44-.16-2.95-.72-2.95-3.2 0-.7.25-1.28.67-1.73-.07-.16-.29-.82.06-1.71 0 0 .54-.17 1.78.66a6.2 6.2 0 0 1 3.24 0c1.23-.83 1.77-.66 1.77-.66.36.89.14 1.55.07 1.71.41.45.66 1.03.66 1.73 0 2.49-1.52 3.04-2.96 3.2.23.2.44.6.44 1.21v1.8c0 .17.12.37.45.31A6.5 6.5 0 0 0 8 1.5z"/></svg> GitHub</a>
        <a class="rbtn" href="/resume.pdf" download><svg width="14" height="14" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2" stroke-linecap="round"><path d="M7 2v8M3 7l4 4 4-4"/><line x1="2" y1="12" x2="12" y2="12"/></svg> Resume</a>
      </div>
    </div>
    <div class="photo">
      <img src="/images/me.jpg" alt="Aaron Su" />
    </div>
  </section>

  <div class="divider"></div>

  <section class="bio mx">
    <div class="slabel">About Me</div>
    <div class="bio-grid">
      <div>
        <p>I'm an <strong>Electrical &amp; Computer Engineering</strong> student at the <a href="https://www.ece.uw.edu/" target="_blank"><em>University of Washington</em></a> with minors in <a href="https://dataminor.uw.edu/" target="_blank"><em>Data Science</em></a> and <a href="https://ischool.uw.edu/" target="_blank"><em>Informatics</em></a>. My work spans the full stack of engineering — from designing PCBs and programming microcontrollers to training custom language models and building cloud infrastructure.</p>
        <p>At the <a href="http://uwseal.com/" target="_blank"><strong>SEAL Lab</strong></a>, I coordinate research and development initiatives, manage DevOps infrastructure supporting ~120 researchers, and am currently training and deploying three custom LLMs for lab-specific workflows. This summer, I'll be joining the <a href="https://xmouyang.github.io/" target="_blank"><strong>MINSys Lab</strong></a> at the <a href="https://hkust.edu.hk/" target="_blank">Hong Kong University of Science and Technology (HKUST)</a>, working on mobile, intelligent, and networked systems.</p>
      </div>
      <div>
        <p>Before engineering, I was a <strong>licensed Emergency Medical Responder</strong> with <strong>Community First Responders</strong>, holding full <a href="https://www2.gov.bc.ca/gov/content/health/about-bc-s-health-care-system/partners/colleges-boards-and-commissions/emergency-medical-assistants-licensing-board/licensing" target="_blank">EMALB Schedule 2 endorsements</a>. Over three years I treated more than 150 patients and supervised first response teams at large-scale events. That experience taught me how to stay calm under pressure, communicate with clarity, and make decisions when the stakes are real.</p>
        <div class="bio-hl">I'm driven by the belief that the best engineers understand problems at every layer — from the silicon to the user interface. Whether it's a CNC-machined robot part or a neural network, I want to build things that matter.</div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <div class="divider"></div>

  <section class="info mx">
    <div>
      <div class="slabel">Education</div>
      <div class="ti">
        <div class="ti-date">Sept 2024 — Jun 2028 (Expected)</div>
        <div class="ti-title">B.S. Electrical &amp; Computer Engineering</div>
        <div class="ti-sub"><a href="https://www.ece.uw.edu/" target="_blank">University of Washington</a> — Seattle, WA</div>
        <div class="ti-desc">Minors in <a href="https://dataminor.uw.edu/" target="_blank">Data Science</a> and <a href="https://ischool.uw.edu/" target="_blank">Informatics</a>. Coursework includes Computer Programming III, PCB Design, Fundamentals of Data Science I, Probability I, 3D Printing, Cybersecurity, and Computer-Communication Networks.</div>
      </div>
      <div class="ti">
        <div class="ti-date">Sept 2019 — Jun 2024</div>
        <div class="ti-title">High School Diploma with Honours</div>
        <div class="ti-sub">J.N. Burnett Secondary School — Richmond, BC</div>
        <div class="ti-desc">GPA: 94/100. Awarded the Member of Parliament Scholarship and the Excellence in Engineering Award.</div>
      </div>
    </div>
    <div>
      <div class="slabel">Experience</div>
      <div class="ti">
        <div class="ti-date">Jun 2026 — Upcoming</div>
        <div class="ti-title">Research Intern</div>
        <div class="ti-sub"><a href="https://xmouyang.github.io/" target="_blank">MINSys Lab</a> — <a href="https://hkust.edu.hk/" target="_blank">HKUST</a>, Hong Kong</div>
        <div class="ti-desc">Joining the Mobile, Intelligent, and Networked System (MINSys) Group under Prof. Xiaomin Ouyang. Developing edge camera systems for real-time detection of high-risk patient behaviors in ICU environments. Designing and optimizing deep learning models for on-device inference under latency, power, and privacy constraints typical of clinical edge deployments. Contributing to publication-oriented research bridging mobile AI systems, computer vision, and healthcare monitoring.</div>
        <div class="ti-badges"><span class="badge">Edge AI</span><span class="badge">Computer Vision</span><span class="badge">Deep Learning</span><span class="badge">Healthcare</span></div>
      </div>
      <div class="ti">
        <div class="ti-date">Sept 2025 — Present</div>
        <div class="ti-title">Student Researcher &amp; AI/ML Engineer</div>
        <div class="ti-sub"><a href="http://uwseal.com/" target="_blank">SEAL Lab</a> — University of Washington</div>
        <div class="ti-desc">Building DevOps infrastructure for ~120 researchers. Training, adapting, and deploying 3 custom LLMs for lab-specific workflows.</div>
        <div class="ti-badges"><span class="badge">Python</span><span class="badge">LLMs</span><span class="badge">DevOps</span></div>
      </div>
      <div class="ti">
        <div class="ti-date">Mar 2022 — Jun 2024</div>
        <div class="ti-title">Emergency Medical Responder</div>
        <div class="ti-sub">Community First Responders — Richmond, BC</div>
        <div class="ti-desc">Licensed EMR in British Columbia with full <a href="https://www2.gov.bc.ca/gov/content/health/about-bc-s-health-care-system/partners/colleges-boards-and-commissions/emergency-medical-assistants-licensing-board/licensing" target="_blank">EMALB Schedule 2 endorsements</a>. Treated 150+ patients over 3 years. Supervised first responder teams at events with 1,000+ attendees. Awarded a City of Richmond Scholarship.</div>
      </div>
      <div class="ti">
        <div class="ti-date">Jan 2022 — Jun 2024</div>
        <div class="ti-title">CNC Specialist — FIRST Robotics</div>
        <div class="ti-sub">J.N. Burnett Secondary — Richmond, BC</div>
        <div class="ti-desc">Designed robot parts for multinational competition. 3rd place regional finish (2022). Led 15 youth in CNC fabrication and skill development.</div>
        <div class="ti-badges"><span class="badge">Fusion 360</span><span class="badge">CNC</span><span class="badge">CAD</span></div>
      </div>
    </div>
